What is YAML ? 
 - Used for data serialisation. Ain't Markup Language 
 - Important for representing data / making our life easier / devops culture / works w
   PyEZ , Ansible and Jsnapy 
 - Human readable 
 - Similar to JSON but much much easier on eyes 
 -  Get to the point 
     '-' - represents Lists 
     ':' - represents dictionaries (maps)
     booleans - true/flase or yes/ no 
     '#' - comments 
     'null/ ' '/ ~' - Empty value 
     '& and << ' - Anchors and aliases - we will not use them for this course 

Lets explore features with example as its the most effective way. 

